Using GNU tools
===============

For more detailed information about the installation process, see INSTALL.

Simple install procedure
------------------------

  > gzip -cd cpptest-@VERSION@.tar.gz | tar xvf -   # unpack the sources
  > cd cpptest-@VERSION@                            # change to the its directory
  > ./configure                                 # run the 'configure' script
  > make                                        # build 'cpptest'

  [ Become root if necessary ]

  > make install

Configuration options
---------------------

The 'configure' script can be given a number of options to enable
and disable various features. For a complete list, type:

  ./configure --help

Under Microsoft Windows
=======================

Windows specific files are found under the 'win' directory. 

If you are using Microsoft Visual Studio, it is suggested that you create an
own project for compiling the library and test program. Do not forget to add an
include path to the 'win' directory.

